  "response": "To improve your chances of getting into an Ivy League school, consider these strategies:\n\n1. Academic Performance\n- Maintain a very high GPA (3.9+)\n- Take challenging courses, especially AP and honors classes\n- Score exceptionally well on SAT/ACT (1500+ on SAT)\n\n2. Extracurricular Activities\n- Develop leadership roles\n- Show deep commitment to a few activities\n- Pursue unique or meaningful experiences\n- Participate in competitions and achievements\n\n3. Personal Development\n- Develop strong writing and communication skills\n- Engage in community service\n- Pursue intellectual passions outside of school\n- Consider research or specialized summer programs\n\n4. Application Strength\n- Write compelling, authentic essays\n- Get strong letters of recommendation\n- Highlight unique personal qualities and experiences\n- Demonstrate passion and potential impact\n\n5. Additional Considerations\n- Learn a foreign language\n- Develop specialized talents or skills\n- Show intellectual curiosity\n- Consider early decision/early action applications\n\n6. Financial Preparation\n- Research financial aid options\n- Prepare financial documentation\n- Understand each school's specific requirements\n\nRemember, Ivy League admissions are highly competitive, so a well-rounded approach is crucial.",
